The Czech Republicâ€™s  PX (PX)  stock index
increased 0.7 percent to 1,018.3 at the end of trading in
 Prague , its second day of gains.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the biggest Czech power utility, rose for
a second day, adding 0.2 percent to 808.8 koruna. Electricity
for next-year delivery in Germany, where CEZ exports part of its
output, advanced 1.1 percent to 53.3 euros per megawatt-hour.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   increased 1.4 percent to 483
koruna, its highest close in three weeks. The Austrian lender
had the price estimate for its Vienna-traded shares raised to
18.7 euros from 15 euros at Nomura International Plc.  Fortuna Entertainment Group NV (FORTUNA)   fell the most
this year after the Czech bookmaker and lottery operator said
its 2011 profit fell 23 percent. The stock slid 2.1 percent to
101 koruna, after rising to a six-month high yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
